text: Aurora Chamorro (11 June 1954 - 17 October 2020) was a Spanish swimmer. She participated in the 1970 European Aquatics Championships, the 1973 World Aquatics Championships and the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich. Chamorro died on 17 October 2020 at the age of 66. ==References== Category:1954 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Spanish swimmers Category:Olympians for Spain
